<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Job Queue - Node.js Interview Playground</title>
    <%- include('partials/styles') %>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <%- include('partials/header') %>
        <%- include('partials/nav') %>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Job Queue - Machine Coding Round</h2>
            
            <h3>Requirements</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>In-memory job queue</li>
                <li>Retry mechanism with exponential backoff</li>
                <li>Priority support</li>
                <li>Failure handling</li>
                <li>Worker processing</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Constraints</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Single process (can extend to distributed)</li>
                <li>Configurable retry attempts</li>
                <li>Configurable delay between retries</li>
            </ul>
            
            <div class="key-points">
                <h3>Interview Discussion Points:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Priority queue implementation</li>
                    <li>Exponential backoff strategy</li>
                    <li>Dead letter queue for failed jobs</li>
                    <li>Distributed job queue with Redis/RabbitMQ</li>
                    <li>Job persistence and recovery</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
